-- Czech Republic Clinches Place in Davis Cup Tennis Semifinals
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-04-07T13:48:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-07/czech-republic-clinches-place-in-davis-cup-tennis-semifinals.html
Defending champion the Czech
Republic clinched a place in the semifinals of tennis’s Davis
Cup today after a win by Lukas Rosol.  Rosol defeated Kazakhstan’s Evgeny Korolev 7-6 (7-5), 6-7
(2-7), 7-6 (7-5), 6-2 in Astana to give the visitors an
unassailable 3-1 lead in the best-of-five event.  In other quarterfinal ties this weekend, Canada leads Italy
2-1 in Vancouver, Serbia is 2-1 up against the U.S. in Boise,
 Idaho , and Argentina leads France by the same score in Buenos
Aires.  The Davis Cup is the top team event in men’s tennis.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 